this? Well, it's one source. So we put it in a fence div, and we give it a class. So in this

00:03:07.440 --> 00:03:15.360
case, that's the chapter intro class. And then for HTML, with the help of meticulous styling

00:03:15.360 --> 00:03:23.119
and with an SCSS file, I write a class for chapter intro and basically give it some things. Like, I

00:03:23.119 --> 00:03:29.919
want some padding, I want some borders, I want some background color, I want an icon. That works

00:03:29.919 --> 00:03:38.479
nicely for HTML, but how do we get it to work for PDF? Well, maybe some of you will recognize this

00:03:38.479 --> 00:03:46.240
with a lot of ambition, coffee, frustration. You can make it happen, and you can get close enough.

00:03:47.199 --> 00:03:53.279
What you're seeing here, even if you've never had to write LaTeX code in this way, and if so,

