00:04:07.199 --> 00:04:14.240
and ultimately try to get them to look as alike as possible. And then Korto allows us to define

00:04:14.240 --> 00:04:21.440
a theme where I pull in this SCSS file, and then for HTML, and also include in the header,

00:04:21.440 --> 00:04:29.440
the style file that I wrote. Now, what is HTML without dark mode, right? So we have to have dark

00:04:29.440 --> 00:04:34.320
mode, obviously, because my students are really willing to study all night long, so they need the

00:04:34.320 --> 00:04:41.040
dark mode. So how do we do this? Another SCSS file where we tweak things minorly and make sure that

00:04:41.040 --> 00:04:47.359
things are still legible, and we pull that in our Korto.yaml file as well. But this all sounds like

