typed. So today, it's one source, two style files, and two outputs. Hopefully, next time I'm touching

00:06:53.359 --> 00:06:59.040
this book, I'll be able to get away with one source, one style file, and two outputs. We'll see.

00:06:59.040 --> 00:07:04.799
If we can get there, great, and if not, that's also fine. But another thing that working with

00:07:04.799 --> 00:07:12.000
these multiple outputs does, in addition to the styling, is sort of your code output. So today,

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:18.399
a lot of the code in the book looks like this. Let's do some data processing to create a table

00:07:18.399 --> 00:07:24.880
and then make a table out of it that will be printed both in HTML and in PDF. And the cable

